Why is React useful for developers? Select all that apply.
  React has a great set of developer tools that make it easier to view our components in the browser and debug what's happening under the hood.
  React allows us to create reusable UI components. 
Correct!

React encourages us to structure our applications as "components": the building blocks of our web page that handle their own data and UI logic, that can be "composed" together with other components to put together a complete app.

  I don't know.
  React allows us to create applications that can change data, without reloading the page.
  It works in many different environments allowing developers to build not only web applications, but mobile applications and server-rendered React.
